{"id":60083,"date":"2024-10-23T15:03:30","date_gmt":"2024-10-23T09:33:30","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=60083"},"modified":"2024-11-25T00:15:53","modified_gmt":"2024-11-24T18:45:53","slug":"single-bed-design","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/single-bed-design\/","title":{"rendered":"5 Single Bed Design Ideas for Compact Homes"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Single bed design ideas that do more than add aesthetic value to your home.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your bedroom is a sacred space that nourishes both the body and mind. So whether you are living in a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/studio-apartment-interior-design-ideas\/\">studio apartment<\/a> or converting your study into a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/guides\/guest-room-design-ideas\/\">guest room<\/a>, the soul of that room is the bed. Don\u2019t let the lack of space upset you because we have a variety of single-bed design ideas that are stylish, functional, and a true celebration of innovative furniture. From foldable sofa chair beds to a simple dewan, these five inspirational ideas will leave you spoilt for choice but refresh your creative vibe. Read on. Read on for more.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Single Bed Designs with Box&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Redoing your not-so-little one\u2019s room? This <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/box-bed-designs\/\">bed box design<\/a> is perfect to accommodate their growing needs while keeping the room clutter-free. Polished in a subtly striking blue, the single bed is an example of remarkable craftsmanship. It allows your independent sleeper to snooze into their wonderful dreamland comfortably. Using the headboard as a shelf allows you to store everyday essentials within reach.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150826\/single-bed-designs-with-box.jpg\" alt=\"Single bed design with built-in box storage maximises the space\" class=\"wp-image-60089\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150826\/single-bed-designs-with-box.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150826\/single-bed-designs-with-box-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150826\/single-bed-designs-with-box-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150826\/single-bed-designs-with-box-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Sensor lights within the box allow easy visibility<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Modern Single Bed Design for Girls&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Your baby girl deserves the best, and this single bed is what dreams are made of. Timelessly stylish so that you don\u2019t need touch-ups from toddler to teenager, the bed features sleek straight lines carved into a space-saving storage shelf. The colour palette of pink and blue minimises gender stereotypes, allowing you to play with beddings of your choice.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150746\/single-bed-design-for-girls.jpg\" alt=\"Charming single bed design for girls in pink and blue with space-saving storage shelf\" class=\"wp-image-60086\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150746\/single-bed-design-for-girls.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150746\/single-bed-design-for-girls-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150746\/single-bed-design-for-girls-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150746\/single-bed-design-for-girls-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The entire bed frame offers ample storage<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Modern Single Bed Design in Wood<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If there was one single bed, we could recommend this one. Oozing subtle elegance, this single bed doubles up as a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/reading-nook\/\">cosy reading nook<\/a>, bringing the corner space together with the entire room. But it doesn\u2019t stop there. The soft hues of white and cream balance off the green bedding by infusing life into the space. A built-in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-drawer-design-ideas\/\">drawer storage<\/a> allows you to hide extra pillows and comforters when hosting, making it the perfect spot to lounge in after a long and tiring day.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150814\/single-bed-design-in-wood.jpg\" alt=\"Elegant single bed designs in wood with a cosy reading nook and built-in storage drawer\" class=\"wp-image-60088\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150814\/single-bed-design-in-wood.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150814\/single-bed-design-in-wood-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150814\/single-bed-design-in-wood-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150814\/single-bed-design-in-wood-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The sliding book cabinet joint to the bed is a brilliant space-saving idea<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Simple Single Bed Design&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A simple plywood single bed design that is fuss-free works almost anywhere in the home. Living room? Make it a stylish dewan. Study? Convert it into an extra bed for guests. Offering limitless versatility, this simple design is also flawless because it comes with pull-out storage drawers that allow you to keep the extra clutter hidden. Placed against a beautiful wall, the warm yellows of the wallpaper create a calming ambience to relax in, while the windows by the headboard allow streaks of natural light to fill the small room with positivity.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150723\/simple-single-bed-design.jpg\" alt=\"Versatile simple single bed design with pull-out storage drawers for clutter-free living\" class=\"wp-image-60084\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150723\/simple-single-bed-design.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150723\/simple-single-bed-design-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150723\/simple-single-bed-design-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150723\/simple-single-bed-design-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">An attractive wallpaper balances the bed\u2019s simple aesthetics<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Single Bed Design for Living Room&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the most challenging areas to style in a small home is the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/\">living room<\/a>, especially if you have to host friends or family overnight. But this elegant sofa-inspired single bed is probably your best bet. The bed offers extra large seating and can be used as a bed for additional hosting needs. This design can be emulated in small homes and studio apartments, too, where the lack of space for a full-blown single bed is most acutely felt.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150800\/single-bed-design-for-living-room.jpg\" alt=\"Stylish single bed design for living room, doubling as a sofa and extra sleeping space\" class=\"wp-image-60087\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150800\/single-bed-design-for-living-room.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150800\/single-bed-design-for-living-room-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150800\/single-bed-design-for-living-room-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/25150800\/single-bed-design-for-living-room-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Opt for fabric prints that match the rest of your home<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Our single-bed design ideas represent versatile yet functional furniture required in modern homes today. Use your personal touch to make the space feel more inviting with small yet impactful changes that match the aesthetics of your home. For more ideas, reach out to us at DesignCafe. We are always happy to help!&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">FAQs on Single Bed Designs<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1. What shall we consider before going for a single bed?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Before choosing your single bed, consider the floor space available in your home. Next, you need to consider the size of the bed, its material and design, its functionality within the house, and your budget.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2. What is the ideal size for a single bed design?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Ideally, single beds are 36 x 75 inches or 39 x 75 inches, but they can vary depending on your choice of material. These sizes are typically for ready-made beds. If you are going to custom-order a single bed, you have the freedom to choose a size according to the space available in your home.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>3. What is the best material for a single bed design?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The most popular single bed material is wood. It is a timeless investment and works well with almost all home layouts. However, if polished, even iron beds last long and ensure easy maintenance.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>4. What is the height of a single bed?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The average height of a single bed is 24 inches from the floor, but it can be up to 36 inches, depending on your preferences.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>5. What should we consider when selecting a single bed for growing children?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>When selecting a single bed for growing children, the size and shape of the bed are important factors to consider. You can choose a single wooden bed with pull-out storage that evolves with them as they gradually outgrow the bed.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Functional Interior Designs?<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with smart